278→  If \(z \notin \overline{\{(x, y)\}}\), there exists opens \(U \subset X\), \(V \subset Y\) such that \(z \notin U \times V\), thus \((x, y) \notin U \times V\). Either \(x \notin U\) or \(y \notin V\), suppose \(x \notin U\). Then \(U \cap \overline{\{x\}} = \emptyset\), thus \(U \times V \cap \overline{\{x\}} \times \overline{\{y\}}  = \emptyset\). This shows that \(\overline{\{x\}} \times \overline{\{y\}} \subseteq \overline{\{(x, y)\}}\).
